m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This +5 sacrificial tongi has a chance to stun creatures of evil {g|Encyclopedia:Alignment}alignment{/g} on {g|Encyclopedia:Critical}critical hits{/g} and grants its wielder the ability to cast chain lightning {g|Encyclopedia:Spell}spell{/g} once per day as a 11th level wizard.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: This is one of the gifts of the royal court master Shaynih'a, who arrived to the Stolen Lands from the foreign land of Vudra in search of her vocation.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: This weapon is a mithral tongi +5.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: An old engraving in Elven indicates that this ritual weapon was created to destroy demons.

m_DescriptionText.LocalisedValue: Whenever the wielder of this +2 corrosive tongi confirms a {g|Encyclopedia:Critical}critical hit{/g} with it, the weapon deals additionally 2 {g|Encyclopedia:Energy_Damage}acid damage{/g} until the end of the combat. This effect stacks.

Whenever the wielder of this +3 sound burst tongi lands a hit, the enemy must pass a {g|Encyclopedia:Saving_Throw}Fortitude saving throw{/g} ({g|Encyclopedia:DC}DC{/g} 23) or become shaken for {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}1d3{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Combat_Round}rounds{/g}.

Whenever the wielder of this +4 anarchic tongi successfully charges at an enemy, the enemy loses its {g|Encyclopedia:Dexterity}Dexterity{/g} {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} to {g|Encyclopedia:Armor_Class}AC{/g} for 1 {g|Encyclopedia:Combat_Round}round{/g}.
This +5 axiomatic shocking burst tongi grants its wearer a +5 competence {g|Encyclopedia:Bonus}bonus{/g} to {g|Encyclopedia:CMB}CMB{/g}.
This is a +1 cold iron ghost touch weapon.

This is a +3 brilliant energy heartseeker weapon. This weapon can tear the soul of a living enemy: whenever it lands a hit, it deals additional {g|Encyclopedia:Dice}1d6{/g} force {g|Encyclopedia:Damage}damage{/g}.

m_FlavorText.LocalisedValue: This weapon was once the seat of Finnean's soul. Now that the soul of the Sarkorian Pathfinder has left the weapon, it has fallen silent forever.
